<1ST_LINE>r a AM-TempleDefaced     04-18 0157</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Temple Defaced,0160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Name Of PLO Leader Painted On Synagogue</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Israel-PLO</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Abu Jihad, the nom de guerre of the
assassinated Palestine Liberation Organization chief, was spray
painted in 2-foot-high letters on the wall of a synagogue here,
police said Sunday.
   The temple also received an obscene, threatening telephone call
shortly after the graffiti was discovered Sunday morning, said
B'nai Torah temple President Lawrence Schechterman.
   PLO military chief Khalil al-Wazir was assassinated Saturday in
Tunisia, and PLO leaders have blamed Israel for the attack.
   ``If they scrawled the name of somebody assassinated yesterday,
I'd say it's a reaction to the assassination,'' said Louise Shure,
regional director of the Anti-Dafamation League of B'nai B'rith in
Palm Beach County. ``Are we going to see more? I hope not.''
   Twenty-four incidents of vandalism have been reported at Florida
synagogues this year as Palestinian unrest has escalated in the
Israeli-occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip.
</TEXT>
