<HEAD>Anti-Israel Protesters Disrupt Commemorative Ceremony</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BASEL, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 50 masked anti-Israeli
demonstrators tried to disrupt a tree planting ceremony marking the
40th anniversary of the Jewish state's founding and this city's
role in the Zionist movement.
   The protesters on Sunday shouted pro-Palestinian slogans, set
off firecrackers and waved a Palestinian flag during a speech on a
city square by Israel's ambassador to Switzerland, Moshe Rivlin.
   Police dispersed the protesters after several minutes.
   The ceremony included the planting of 40 cedars donated by
Israel to the city of Basel, host of the first Zionist World
Congress in 1897.
   At a separate rally, local leftist politicians and activists
charged the city was endorsing Israel's Arab policies by accepting
the gift.
   At least 166 Palestinians have been killed in four months of
violent Arab protests in the Israeli-occupied West Bank and Gaza
Strip.
