<1ST_LINE>u w PM-USWarships     04-18 0206</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-US Warships,200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With PM-Gulf-Shelling</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The American warships used to attack two
Iranian oil platforms early this morning included a cruiser and two
destroyers in addition to smaller frigates, according to the
Pentagon.
   The attack on the Sirri oil platform in the gulf was led by the
cruiser Wainwright, a 547-foot warship commissioned in 1966 that
carries a variety of missiles in addition to a five-inch gun.
   The Wainwright attacked along with two frigates, the Simpson and
Bagley. The Simpson is a so-called Oliver Hazard Perry-class ship _
identical to the Samuel B. Roberts, which hit a mine last week. The
Bagley is a much older vessel, commissioned in 1972.
   The Pentagon said the Sassan oil platform was attacked by two
destroyers _ the Merrill and the Lynde McCormick. The two warships
were accompanied by the amphibious landing ship Trenton.
   The Trenton carries helicopters, but it was not immediately
clear whether they had played any role in the attack.
   The Merrill is a so-called Spruance-class destroyer,
commissioned in 1978 and armed with the same type of five-inch guns
as those found on the Wainwright. The Lynde McCormick also carries
five-inch guns for shelling, but is much older. It was commissioned
in 1961.
</TEXT>
