Catholics in Lithuania to profess their faith without
discrimination.
   The pope recalled last year's celebration of 600 years of
Christianity in Lithuania, but also noted what he called ``the
profound hardships'' still suffered by the Lithuanian church.
   He said those problems include the difficulties in carrying out
its pastoral mission without legal recognition and wif priests and bishops.
   Vatican statistics indicate there are nearly 2 million Catholics
in Lithuania, but th a shortage
oonly 575 priests for 543 parishes.
