<HEAD>Reagan Names National Security Assistant, Legislative Aide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan on Monday named Nelson C.
Ledsky as a special assistant for national security affairs and
senior director of the European and Soviet affairs directorate.
   Ledsky succeeds Fritz W. Earmarth in the National Security
Council post.
   A graduate of Western Reserve University in Cleveland and
