<1ST_LINE>r a AM-GuardsmenMissing     04-18 0190</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Guardsmen Missing,0193</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Search Called Off for Guardsmen Missing in Lake Erie</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A search for two Ohio National Guardsmen
missing for more than a day in Lake Erie was canceled Monday night
after searchers failed to find the men.
   Lt. George Dupree of the U.S. Coast Guard's Cleveland office
said the Coast Guard did not plan to resume the search, conducted
by Coast Guard units from the United States and Canada and National
Guard personnel.
   ``Unless we find more evidence that would warrant our going out
and searching, we won't be going out again.''
   The missing guardsmen were on one of two patrol boats sent out
from Camp Perry on Sunday to clear an area about five miles out of
civilian boats before the start of the 4th U.S. Army rifle matches.
Start of the matches was suspended until a search was finished.
   National Guard spokesman Don Lundy said the men are members of
the 837th Engineer Co., which has its headquarters at St. Marys.
They were identified as Sgt. Melvin E. Wisecup, 31, of Waynesfield,
and Spec. 4 Wayne C. Wingate, 30, of Lima.
</TEXT>
