<HEAD>Nynex Earnings Rise 3.4 Percent</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Nynex Corp., the regional Bell telephone holding company for New
York and New England, said Monday its profit rose 3.4 percent in
the first three months of 1988.
   Nynex said it earned $311.1 million, or $1.55 a share, up from
$299.2 million, or $1.47 a share, in the same period of 1987.
Revenue rose 6.2 percent to $3.07 billion from $2.89 billion a year
earlier.
   Chairman D.C. Staley said the company was experiencing healthy
demand for services and was continuing to control expenses.
</TEXT>
