index; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices on the London Stock Exchange ended
higher Monday, but well below their midday highs because of Wall
Street's weak opening.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed up 9.2
points, or 0.5 percent, at 1,787.8.
   The index had been up as much as 23.8 points around midday.
   Volume was a light 416.9 million shares, down from 472.9 million
Friday.
